<title>SINGAPORE: Singapore May retail sales rise 1.0 pct on year.</title>
<headline>Singapore May retail sales rise 1.0 pct on year.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-07-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Singapore's retail sales index (base 1991) rose 1.0 percent in May compared to a year ago, the Statistics Department said on Sunday.</p>
<p>The index was up 4.5 percent compared with April.</p>
<p>Excluding motor vehicles, the index registered a month-on-month gain of 5.9 percent in May.</p>
<p>Total May retail sales were estimated at Singapore $2.073 billion.</p>
<p>The report said that year-on-year, in constant prices, the retail index rose by 3.0 percent.  </p>
<p>					 Month-on-month     Yr-on-yr</p>
<p>    Total index			    4.5		 1.0</p>
<p>    X-vehicle sales			5.9		 5.6</p>
<p>    Textiles/apparels		    0.4		 4.2</p>
<p>    Furniture/household equipment    6.5		10.7</p>
<p>    Motor vehicles			-0.7	     -13.4</p>
<p>    Petrol stations			0.9		-1.5</p>
<p>    Department stores/supermarkets  11.6		 3.8</p>
<p>    General provisions		   4.4		 6.0</p>
<p>    Other retail			   6.9		 7.5</p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 8703080)</p>
